This paper deals with exploring the entropy region of four random variables, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of multiobjective optimization and linear programming, which are topics related to computer science (cs.DS) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also involves experimental results and algorithm design, which are topics related to computational engineering (cs.CE) and data mining (cs.DM).
